cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on developing a novel algorithm for making CNN-based models interpretable by visualizing input regions that are important for predictions, especially for biomedical 3D imaging data inputs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of gradients and feature maps, which are common techniques in deep learning and machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with 3D imaging data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
